This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a novel computational model for visual action recognition. Additionally, the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests that it may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper's focus on feedback and lateral connections in the primate visual cortex suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of natural language processing techniques in the abstract suggests that it may also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
